#   BLAME-006a: blame skips a deleted file instead of folding an empty layer (root mis-attribution)

`be blame:` attributes lines to the ROOT commit for a file that was DELETED then
RE-ADDED, because the blame weave SKIPS the delete instead of folding an empty
(delete) layer â€” so the old tokens never die and the readd's structurally-equal
tokens (titles, blank lines) inherit the root commit's seq. Split from
[BLAME-006] (the correctness half). Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Repro: `be blame:ABC.md` pins 5 pieces to `?c7184818#initial` (root). `ABC.md`
    was a DIFFERENT doc at root, DELETED at `006b9039` (18Nov24 reorg), RE-ADDED as
    the current doc at `8948262e` (22May, its true add commit, owns 20/28). The 5
    root-pinned pieces are line-1 H1 + 4 blank lines before `##` headers â€” content-only
    RAPHash (`BLAME/WEAVE.c:502,510`) COLLIDES across the delete/readd.
 -  Root cause: `graf/BLAME.c:480` (`if (dr==BLAME_DESC_ABSENT) continue;`) + twin
    `:492` â€” when the path is absent at a commit, `GRAFFileWeave` SKIPS it instead
    of folding an empty layer, so old tokens stay alive; the readd content folds and
    the WEAVE EQ keep-seq branch (`WEAVE.c:579-586`) matches new title/blank tokens
    to the still-alive root tokens â†’ they inherit root's seq.

### Goals
 -  A delete is folded as an explicit empty (all-delete) layer so tokens DIE at the
    delete commit â†’ a readd is a clean all-INS at the readd commit; no root leak.
 -  `be blame:ABC.md` attributes all pieces to `8948262e`+ (or their real authors),
    none to root.

### Constraints
 -  Behaviour-preserving for files that were never deleted: `GRAFblameident` /
    `GRAFblameruns` byte-identical. graf change gates for review.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Reuse the existing all-delete path (`WEAVE.c:534-540`, `nlen==0`): at
    `BLAME.c:480/492`, on `BLAME_DESC_ABSENT`, fold an EMPTY version (all tokens
    deleted) rather than `continue`.

